<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 17 at 9:59PM CDT  by NWS Bismarck</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT PORTIONS OF NORTHERN PIERCE
COUNTY THROUGH 1100 PM CDT...
At 959 PM CDT, a strong thunderstorm was located near Barton, or 8
miles northwest of Rugby, moving southeast at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Rugby.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
